headline: Walmart earnings, FedSpeak, housing data: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime Anchors Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton preview key events for Tuesday, November 19, 2024. Many companies are set to report quarterly results, including retail giants Walmart (WMT) and Lowe's (LOW), alongside Viking Holdings (VIK), XPeng (XPEV), Medtronic (MDT), and La-Z-Boy (LZB). Investors also await the release of Housing Starts & Building Permits data, which will offer a fresh perspective on the housing market's health and construction activity. Additionally, investors will hear from Chicago Fed president Austan Goolsbee, who is scheduled to speak tomorrow afternoon. This comes after Fed Chair Jerome Powell's recent comments that the central bank was in "no hurry" to cut rates. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Angel Smith
